SIMPLE: intended
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intended
<hw>In*tend"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made tense;
stretched out; extended; forcible; violent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Purposed; designed; <as>as, <ex>intended</ex> harm
or help</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They drew a curse from an <qex>intended</qex> good.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Betrothed; affianced; <as>as, an <ex>intended</ex>
husband</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intended</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intended
<hw>In*tend"ed</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One with whom marriage is
designed; one who is betrothed; an affianced lover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If it were not that I might appear to disparage his
<qex>intended</qex>, . . . I would add that to me she seems to be
throwing herself away.</q> <rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intendedly</ent>⟦br⟧
